{
  "texts": [
    "Unlike heuristic methods, MinerU-HTML understands semantic context and preserves document structure, enabling high-fidelity extraction of main content while maintaining formulas, code blocks, and tables.Our comprehensive evaluation demonstrates that extraction quality significantly impacts downstream model capabilities:1.",
    "Extraction Quality Matters: On WebMainBench, our newly constructed benchmark of 7,887 annotated web pages, MinerU-HTML achieves a ROUGE-N F1 score of 0.8182, substantially outperform-ing Trafilatura (0.6358).",
    "For structured element preservation, MinerU-HTML achieves 0.9093 edit similarity for code blocks and 0.9399 for formulas, compared to 0.1305 and 0.6107 for Trafilatura.",
    "Corpus-Level Quality Improvement:A direct comparison on 10,000 document pairs from Common Crawl, evaluated via an LLM-as-judge, shows AICC is preferred over its Trafilatura-based counterpart (TfCC) with a 72.0% win rate.",
    "This confirms that MinerU-HTML's extraction improvements on the benchmark generalize to the full corpus.3."
  ]
}